cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.IT

This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of wireless networks, specifically the placement of extenders to maximize throughput. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also heavily relies on artificial intelligence techniques, such as case-based reasoning and optimization algorithms, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of sensing and perception in the network, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
